                <h1>Exploring Comic Book Dots: The Art of Ben-Day Technique</h1>
                <p>Comic book dots, known as Ben-Day dots, are a technique used to create shading and color in comic art. These small, colored dots are arranged in patterns to allow for color variation and depth without the need for extensive color printing. This iconic method defined the visual style of classic comics, making them instantly recognizable.</p>
